<chapter id="faq" status="review">
<title>Frequently Asked Questions</title>
	<sect1 id="faq-keyring" status="review">
		<title>Gnome Keyring asks for my password whenever I log in</title>
		<para>If you want to allow all users access to the network connection:</para>
		<orderedlist>
			<listitem><para>Right click the <guiicon>NetworkManager</guiicon> icon in the system notification area and click <guilabel>Edit Connections...</guilabel></para></listitem>
			<listitem><para>Click the wireless tab.</para></listitem>
			<listitem><para>Click the connection you want to allow access to and click <guibutton>edit</guibutton>.</para></listitem>
			<listitem><para>Tick the "Available to all users" checkbox.</para></listitem>
			<listitem><para>You will be asked for your password.</para></listitem>
			<listitem><para>Click the <guibutton>Apply</guibutton> then <guibutton>Close</guibutton>.</para></listitem>
		</orderedlist>
	</sect1>
